<h2 style="margin-bottom: 35px;">Advancing <b>open-source</b> agile management - one <span style="color: green;">/project</span> at a time.<br/> <font color="#ccc">(First release - coming soon!)</font></h2>
</center>

<div class="featured">
<p style="margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 35px;"><strong>SocialPM</strong> is a Socially-focused OpenSource Agile Project Management Platform - providing enhanced productivity for distributed or co-located Agile project teams. SocialPM respects the simplicity of the Agile methodology, without restricting your processes or patterns, and includes features such as: stories, tasks, burndown charts, the product backlog, iterations and releases, team assignments, <a href="#features">and more</a>. We welcome all developers to <a href="https://github.com/ocpsoft/socialpm">get involved in the project &raquo;</a></p>
</div>

<center>
<p style="margin: 20px;">Come join us on in <code>#SocialPM</code> - <a href="http://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=%23socialpm" title="SocialPM channel on Freenode IRC" target="_blank">our channel on irc.freenode.net.</a> Additionally, you are welcome to attend the dev meeting, every other [[Calendar|Tuesday at 5pm EST]]. Also, please join the discussion on our <a href="mailto:socialpm-dev@googlegroups.com">dev email list</a>.</p>
</center>

<a name="features"></a>
<h2>Features</h2>
<table width="100%">
<tr><td width="50%"><ul>
	<li>Backlogs *</li>
	<li>Burn-up & burn-down Charts *</li>
	<li>Collaboration via eMail *</li>
	<li>Front and Back Burners</li>
	<li>Impediment Tracking</li>
	<li>Instant Status Notifications *</li>
	<li>Intuitive Presentation</li>
	<li>Iteration Planning and History *</li>
</ul>
</td><td>
<ul>
	<li>OpenID Support (Log in with Google)</li>
	<li>Organizations and Teams *</li>
	<li>Release Planning *</li>
	<li>Runs on the JBoss AS7 Application Server</li>
	<li>Streamlined HTML5 Interface</li>
	<li>Story Planning</li>
	<li>Tasks, Assignments, and Validation Criteria</li>
	<li>Create embedded dashboards</li>
</ul></td></tr>

